# Authentication Configuration (Optional - Future Feature)
# ============================================================================
# Enable JWT-based authentication to protect your RFP analysis server.
# When disabled, server runs in guest mode (full access, no login required).
#
# SECURITY USE CASES:
# - Team deployments: Multiple users with different access levels
# - Production environments: Protect sensitive RFP analysis data
# - Client deployments: Secure access to proposal intelligence
#
# To enable authentication:
# 1. Uncomment and configure AUTH_ACCOUNTS below
# 2. Set TOKEN_SECRET to a secure random string
# 3. Restart server - /login endpoint will be active
# 4. WebUI will show login screen
#
# Multi-user configuration format:
# AUTH_ACCOUNTS={"username1": "password1", "username2": "password2", "admin": "secure-password"}
#
# Example configurations:
#
# Single user (simple):
# AUTH_ACCOUNTS={"admin": "your-secure-password"}
#
# Multiple users (team deployment):
# AUTH_ACCOUNTS={"alice": "pass123", "bob": "pass456", "admin": "admin-pass"}
